                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>over which he has been called to preside whose branches extend to\n                                        every quarter<lb/> of the habitable globe.–In the discharge\n                                        of that duty then the grand<lb/> Master of\n                                                  <placeName>England</placeName> protest against the\n                                        refusal which has been made<lb/> to acknowledge the\n                                        legitimate children of a lawfully constituted En-<lb/>glish\n                                        Lodge. and at the same time is constrained to recall from\n                                        his<lb/> post the R W mother the <persName>Chev\n                                                  Esser</persName> as the representative of\n                                                  <placeName>England</placeName> in<lb/> the G L R Y\n                                        of <placeName>Russia</placeName> at\n                                                  <placeName>Berlin</placeName> x x x x x x The\n                                        Grand Master com-<lb/>mands me to add that he has\n                                        communicated to the G L the<lb/> sentiments here conveyed,\n                                        as well as the cause he felt compelled to<lb/> adopt and\n                                        that the G L with one record declared its full accents<lb/>\n                                        x x x x x he laments the occurrences which for a time,\n                                        unfortu-<lb/>nately impede the wanted intercourse x x x x\n                                        dated <placeName>London</placeName>\n                                        <date>4 Sept 1846</date><lb/> ([)The periodical from which\n                                        the above is extracted among other very liberal<lb/> and\n                                        pertinent remarks in this noble letter and the\n                                                  <placeName>Berlin</placeName> reply<lb/> observes\n                                        \"The letter itself\" (meaning the\n                                                  <placeName>Berlin</placeName> reply) \"occupying 4\n                                                  <sic>Loges</sic> is<lb/> not worth recording and\n                                        we have no wish to <del>plase upon record that it</del>\n                                        promulgate so<lb/> unmasonic a <del>record</del> document,\n                                        nor do we wish to place upon record<lb/> that which we know\n                                        the Prussian Freemasons are ashamed of \"x x x x<lb/> In the\n                                        meantime it it affords us great pleasure to be able to\n                                        state<lb/> that the members of the Pilgrim Lodge of\n                                                  <placeName>London</placeName> No 289 which\n                                        works<lb/> in the German Language and of which the late\n                                        Prussian representative<lb/> brother\n                                                  <persName>Hebeler</persName> was master have since\n                                        the publicity given to the anti-<lb/>-masonic Prussian\n                                        doctrine altered their mode of initiation and do not<lb/>\n                                        now compel the candidate to make a declaration of his\n                                        religion<lb/> previously to his being admitted, we were\n                                        surprised at its not being<lb/> altered before, considering\n                                        the immediate P G R of <placeName>England</placeName> is a\n                                        mem-<lb/>ber of the Lodge.–The Most Worshipful Master's\n                                        determined conduct<lb/> has already produced a good effect.\n                                        All honor to him, as well as to<lb/> brother <persName>Henry\n                                                  Faudel</persName> the stalwart champion of the\n                                        Jewish Free-<lb/>masons\"–([)It is proper to add that this\n                                        gentleman, (<persName>Henry Faudel</persName>)<lb/> is\n                                        himself a Jew partner brotherinlaw to <del>the</del>\n                                        <persName>Mr B Phillips</persName> the<lb/> recently elected\n                                        common Council man of whose appointment I have<lb/>\n                                        furnished you with an account above. <del>The</del></p>\n                              <p>The Great Synagogue Dukes place has had the liberality and\n                                        good<lb/> taste to vote <del>the ?</del> an increase of\n                                                  <del>the</del> salary<lb/> to the Chief Rabbi, the\n                                        other German synagogues are expected to<lb/> contribute in\n                                        their due proportions.–It is proposed also to augment</p>"
                  },
