                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the present inadequate stipends of the Dayanim who considering<lb/>\n                                        the dignity and importance of their respective duties have\n                                        hitherto–<lb/>been but very indifferently hard.–The \"Jewish\n                                        Chronicle\" gives<lb/> a very ample and interesting report of\n                                        an <del>very</del> important meeting<lb/> held at Liverpool\n                                        to celebrate the anniversary of the \"Hebrew\n                                        Phil<lb/>anthropic Society\" at which some very eloquent\n                                        speeches men made<lb/> on the subject of Jewish Emancipation\n                                        by the <persName>Revd Dr Raphael</persName><lb/> of\n                                                  <placeName>Birmingham</placeName>, <persName>H I\n                                                  Atkinson Esquire</persName> an eminent Barrister\n                                        several<lb/> other distinguished Jews Christians. the great\n                                        length to which I<lb/> have already entered this\n                                        communication precludes the possible<lb/> of my making any\n                                        extract but as I presume you regularly re-<lb/>ceive the\n                                        Anglo Jewish periodicals I beg to call your attention<lb/>\n                                        to this report as contained in the \"Jewish Chronicle.\"–</p>\n                              <p>The committee of the Jews General Literary Scientific\n                                        Institution<lb/> have put forth a very tempting programme\n                                        for their anniversary<lb/> fete which will come off on the\n                                        20th Inst. I shall endeavour<lb/> to give you some account\n                                        of it in my next. The Portuguese<lb/> Beth Holim Hospital\n                                        Ball will take place the night succeeding<lb/> they are both\n                                        deserving objects–and will I trust meet with the<lb/> best\n                                        encouragement.–This is also the season for holiding<lb/> the\n                                        anniversaries of several other Jewish Institutions\n                                        namely<lb/> the Blind Asylum, Infant School Orphan Asylum\n                                        each<lb/> of which is celebrated by a grand Public Ball.–I\n                                        shall refer<lb/> more particularly to some of these\n                                        Charities in my future cor-<lb/>respondence\n                                        <del>also</del>.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(11)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">O.</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <div>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_4_10.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text refers to Occident Volume 4 No. 10 pages 515\n                                                  through 516. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                              </div>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
